# Files that don't belong in the Vercel static + /api deploy.
# Everything the Node server needs stays in the repo for local dev
# (and any Node-capable host deployment via DEPLOYMENT.md) — but isn't shipped to Vercel.

# Node server (Express app, not used on Vercel)
server/
admin/
scripts/
data/
public/uploads/

# Dev / CI tooling
.github/
.githooks/
ci/
.agents/
.claude/
node_modules/

# Secrets + runtime state
.env
.env.local
*.log
*.log.*

# Media that doesn't belong in git (already gitignored but safety-net)
*.mov
*.mp4
*.MOV
*.MP4

# Misc
.DS_Store
auto-push.sh
frame_A_reference.jpg
frame_B_reference.jpg
remotion/
skills-lock.json

# Docs — deploy-facing ones (README) stay; internal ops docs can stay too, they're harmless
# (Uncomment to exclude them from the deploy bundle if you prefer.)
# DEPLOYMENT.md
# SECURITY.md
# PRODUCTION_CHECKLIST.md
# INCIDENT_TEMPLATE.md
